OL,3,CCharities urge people to stop donating
OL,4,Cbroken and low-quality items
OL,6,FCharities across the Channel Islands
OL,7,Fare urging people to think twice about
OL,8,Fwhat they donate after seeing a rise
OL,9,Fin low-quality and broken items.
OL,11,FThey say it costs them time and money
OL,12,Fto throw away every product and while
OL,13,Fthey appreciate the thought,
OL,14,Funsellable donations hinder rather
OL,15,Fthan help them.
OL,17,FOn the days Jersey's La Collette
OL,18,FRecycling Centre is closed, a charity
OL,19,Ftold ITV News that it sees a rise in
OL,20,Flow-quality donations.
