OL,3,CCharities urge people to stop donating
OL,4,Cbroken and low-quality items
OL,6,FRobert Mackenzie from Guernsey's
OL,7,FFriends of Citizens Advice Charity
OL,8,FShop adds that their store can take
OL,9,Felectrical products as they PAT test
OL,10,Fthem to ensure they are safe to
OL,11,Fresell, but they cannot do anything
OL,12,Fwith faulty items.
OL,14,FHe explains: "Cables are missing,
OL,15,Fplugs are missing, the essential part
OL,16,Fto make the product work. We do really
OL,17,Fneed those bits and pieces
OL,18,Ffundamentally for it to be sold again.
