OL,3,CCharities urge people to stop donating
OL,4,Cbroken and low-quality items
OL,6,F"On clothing, people come in with
OL,7,Fpaint on them or ripped. Basically, if
OL,8,Fyou don't want to wear it, does
OL,9,Fanybody else?"
OL,11,FDarren Arnold, Operations Manager at
OL,12,FJersey's Acorn Charity Shop, says
OL,13,Fdamaged items are a hassle and can cut
OL,14,Finto their bottom line.
